  <source>Imperial College London</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Zinc carnosine is a food supplement which is available in the health food shops. The
      investigators wish to see if it can reduce intestinal swelling in people who take
      non-steroidal anti-inflammatory (anti-swelling) drugs (NSAIDs).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
